 OONI of Ife Oba Adeyeye Enitan Ogunwusi, Ojaja II has donated two motorised fumigating machine to Rivers State Government to contain the spread of the Coronavirus pandemic. Presenting the equipment to Governor Nyesom Wike at Government House, Port Harcourt yesterday, the Oba Ogunwusi said they were locally fabricated to combat the coronavirus disease in the country. The monarch, who was represented by a member of Ooni of Ife COVID 19 Taskforce, Princess Fadekemi Fadojutimi, said the equipment, which uses sodium hydrochloride solution, would assist the government in its fight against the virus. He lauded Wike for his pragmatic approach in containing the spread of the pandemic. Wike, who was represented by the Commissioner for Health, Prof. Princewill Chike, thanked the Ooni for his kind gesture. He also hailed the monarch for the patriotic zeal, which inspired him to make the donation and called for the emulation of the innovation that inspired the fabrication.  